The paper deals with the analysis and modelling of a real-life financial loan application using probabilistic models. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of incomplete event logs on decision models, which could fall under the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper explores the use of quantum-like probabilistic inferences, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
